        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 8:37PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>Temperatures have fallen to 32 degrees or so across portions of
Schenectady and Albany Counties early this evening. Some
intermittent light freezing rain or drizzle may cause light ice
accumulations on untreated surfaces. Some slick spots may be
encountered on some roads or sidewalks.

Temperatures will start to warm back above freezing around
midnight, as a warm front begins to move back northward across
the region. The precipitation will change back to plain rain.
</description>
